headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma scored 36 points, and the Washington Wizards overcame the absence of Bradley Beal and Kristaps Porzingis to beat the Dallas Mavericks 113-105 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kuzma scores 36 to lead Wizards past Mavericks 113-105

headlines.description: — A sloppy offensive game left the Atlanta Hawks looking for a better finish and the Philadelphia 76ers looking for better play at point guard.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young helps Hawks pull away in 2nd half, beat 76ers 104-95

headlines.description: — Another night, another close game for the Miami Heat. And Jimmy Butler wouldn't let this one get away.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler scores 35, Heat hold off Hornets 117-112 in OT

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Jerami Grant dribbled between his legs, knifed between New Orleans forwards Zion Williamson and Brandon Ingram and dunked hard with two hands before defenders Herb Jones and Trey Murphy III could meet him at the rim.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grant, Blazers win again on the road, 106-95 over Pelicans
